Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,这是我爹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.34,0:00:06.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,他就要完成他最近一直在忙的一项工作啦 就是 詹姆斯韦伯太空望远镜!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.34,0:00:06.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,以下简称"JWST"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.72,0:00:09.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST的遮阳罩~
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.54,0:00:12.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,大家好 我是《天天大聪明》频道的Destin
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.02,0:00:15.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST就要上天啦
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.06,0:00:19.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,这可是全球科学界一直心心念念的大事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.11,0:00:22.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,反正我做字幕的时候还没(
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.11,0:00:22.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,等大家刷到这个视频的时候 可能它已经上天了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:24.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,甚至可能已经在轨运行多年了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.82,0:00:32.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过这不重要 因为我今天要与一位特别的人对话 并学习很多JWST相关的内容
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.69,0:00:36.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST(部署后)体积过大 无法装进任何火箭整流罩
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.85,0:00:42.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以为了把它送到太空 必须先把它折叠成更紧凑的形状
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.59,0:00:45.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,发射后 它会像折纸作品一样慢慢展开
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:49.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,而在我眼里 这简直是设计精妙的工程奇迹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.83,0:00:52.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,你不但要保证这一系列流程都能顺利完成
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:57.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,还要保证这些结构能经受火箭发射时剧烈的震动环境
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.27,0:01:00.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,像JWST这样规模的工程
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.92,0:01:05.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,不但立项和制造要花很久 任务执行也要相当久 简直叹为观止
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.53,0:01:10.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,大家刚刚已经见过我爹了 即使他不在这干活我也会为JWST感到震撼的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.92,0:01:14.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,但他的努力让我更加觉得这件事有着特别的意义
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.08,0:01:18.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,而下期视频我将详细讲讲我爹具体在遮阳罩上做了哪些工作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.61,0:01:21.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为真的太牛逼了 有太多值得学习的东西了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.07,0:01:27.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,但首先我想先了解一下JWST到底是什么 它的各项重要内容是如何完成的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.07,0:01:30.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们要找一位大佬聊聊这些
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:36.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,2017年的时候我很荣幸到了戈达德太空飞行中心
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.36,0:01:40.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,又极其幸运得以和一位在这个项目里工作的大佬进行对话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:42.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,这位大佬就是约翰·马瑟博士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.41,0:01:46.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,在对话开始之前 我想先向大家介绍一下这位大佬
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:52.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果你想从全人类里挑一个人给你介绍JWST
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.19,0:01:54.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,那你肯定会选约翰·马瑟博士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.33,0:01:56.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,原因其一 他是一位天体物理学家和宇宙学家
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.96,0:02:03.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,他还凭借和George Smoot在宇宙背景探测者卫星的工作获得了诺贝尔物理奖
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.18,0:02:06.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,我想表达的是 没有人比他更懂头顶这片星空了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.17,0:02:11.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,而天文学家们一直在苦苦寻找膨胀宇宙的中心 却一直毫无踪迹
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:15.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,想象一个无限的宇宙正在无限地向自己扩张
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.85,0:02:18.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,没有边界 没有中心 也没有边缘
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.68,0:02:25.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,原因其二 他是整个JWST项目的首席科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.36,0:02:30.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,这意味着他代表着科学侧的利益 来担任项目首席科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:34.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,而鉴于他脑中所知道的东西 也鉴于整个项目都是科研相关的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.98,0:02:38.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,大家就能想象他的意见有多么重要了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.27,0:02:44.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,不只是因为我们在和一个充满智慧的灵魂对话 他还非常善良
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.66,0:02:49.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如我做采访的时候 其实那次采访并不是做过的最好的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.53,0:02:54.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,我当时在一个小会议中心的边屋 想要拍他 但我的相机一直在过热
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:58.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,而他则非常耐心 希望大家也能这样耐心
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.28,0:03:00.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,他的解释真的很通俗易懂
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.74,0:03:05.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们在用最简单的语言去解释人类建造过的最复杂的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:11.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,稍后的对话过程中我会中间插几句话 还会简单画两笔~挺有意思的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.57,0:03:12.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,那么我们开始吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.70,0:03:18.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们去和参与建造JWST的伟大灵魂对话吧~让我们走进本期《天天大聪明》~
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:25.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,那么这位就是约翰·马瑟博士啦
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.21,0:03:28.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,-我可以称呼您尊敬的诺奖得主吗? -可以呀
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:32.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,-您愿意和我们讲讲JWST吗? -我很乐意 -我们坐下聊吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:42.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,我想做的是 在您同意的情况下 做一个关于JWST的系列视频
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.08,0:03:42.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,OK~
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.66,0:03:45.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,-而您就是JWST的幕后大佬? -呃……我只是参与者之一
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.75,0:03:48.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,我从项目一开始就是首席项目科学家了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:52.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,您的大名吾辈早有耳闻 为人谦逊 从不居功自傲
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.87,0:04:01.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,我的确为我们所做的事情感到自豪 但显然这是一个团队项目 非常庞大的团队项目
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.13,0:04:05.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就是望远镜的外形图啦 你可以看到……
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.42,0:04:13.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,它看起来完全不像一个望远镜 既不像当年伽利略用过的那款 也不像哈勃望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.60,0:04:18.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,远远待在太空 更像是一个汇聚太阳能的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.23,0:04:23.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,它有着巨大的六边形主镜 由18块小六边形组成
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.57,0:04:27.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,用来收集我笔指的方向来的遥远星系的光
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.20,0:04:33.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,经过主镜反射 再经过这里的一块小凸面镜反射 回到这里黑色的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:35.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这里是设备组件的起点
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:37.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,这种结构是叫卡塞格兰反射镜吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.56,0:04:40.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,这两部分构成了卡塞格兰反射镜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.37,0:04:41.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,这里面还有第三块镜子 图里看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.79,0:04:45.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,构成一套三反射镜消像散望远镜 性能更好
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:46.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,抱歉我没听清?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:48.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,三反射镜消像散系统
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:49.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,这我得好好查查
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.59,0:04:53.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样的系统可以有更大的有效视场
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.41,0:04:54.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,懂了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:59.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,这点对我们很重要 因为我们想要更好的成像质量 又有这么大的反射镜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.03,0:05:00.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,我回来的确查了一下这个东西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:05.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,三反射镜消像散系统 Three-mirror anastigmat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.35,0:05:12.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,简单来讲 光在到达拍摄的传感器之前会经过三次反射
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:15.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,每次反射都有专门的目的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:17.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,第一块主镜 就像大水桶一样
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:21.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,把来自宇宙的各种光都收集起来并汇聚
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:24.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以他们希望这块镜子越大越好
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:26.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为更大的面就能收集更多的光
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.64,0:05:33.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,从巨大的主镜反射来的光会汇聚到它前面的一块很小的二级镜面上
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.50,0:05:40.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,你们想想这一大块主镜能比二级的小镜子多收集多少宇宙里的光
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:46.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有光会反射进望远镜内 经过三级镜面的反射后来到微调镜上
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.65,0:05:51.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,这块镜子会补偿航天器移动带来的误差 功能类似相机的稳定器
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.73,0:05:56.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,经过这一切光学组件后 就到了整个三反射镜消像散系统得到图像的地方了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:06:02.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然叫"三反射镜"消像散系统 但其实里面有第四个反射镜充当稳定器 懂了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.37,0:06:05.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,建造最难的地方就是这块巨大的主镜
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:06.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为它由18块小镜子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.15,0:06:13.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,全部要在望远镜进入太空后再调整到正确的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:18.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们都是由铍制造的 非常轻 非常坚硬 且在低温下不会变形
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.80,0:06:21.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,最难的地方也正在此 因为我们要让它非常非常非常轻
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.92,0:06:24.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,每一小块六边形镜面 都轻到用手就能提起来
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.89,0:06:26.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果我们让你上手的话
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.93,0:06:30.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以它们的材料真的又薄又精确
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:33.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,在镜面部分后 是设备组件
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.51,0:06:35.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,里面有相机和光谱仪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.41,0:06:37.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了这两样东西我们还研发了一堆新玩意
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:39.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们之前需要更高标准的检测器
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.58,0:06:47.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,而检测器有两种重要原料 一种叫碲镉汞 一种叫掺砷硅
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:52.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,这两种物质可以让我们的研究有更高的灵敏度 更广范围的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:56.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,-而这些东西之前都还不存在? -存在倒是存在 但达不到我们的需求
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.50,0:06:59.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,灵敏度不够 尺寸太小
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:07:00.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以这方面研发投入了不少
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.93,0:07:05.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,另一个显而易见的难点就是这么大一块东西该怎么造?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:08.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,我指的这块 就是遮阳罩
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:11.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,由五层镀有金属的塑料膜组成
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.18,0:07:11.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,聚酰亚胺?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.85,0:07:18.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,对 所以太阳光是从下面照过来的 就全反射走了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:25.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,只有极少数的热量会渗透过来 我们想让望远镜保持低温 保持稳定
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.44,0:07:31.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以到了太空望远镜的飞行姿态大概是这样 太阳一直照着它底面的设备组件
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.29,0:07:33.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,光学镜面部分保持在阴影中
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.10,0:07:38.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,就好像在地球上我们只能在星球阴影中 也就是晚上才能看到星星
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.91,0:07:43.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这块巨大的遮阳罩也能为望远镜营造出持续的"夜晚"环境
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.49,0:07:47.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,望远镜的一侧一直在黑暗中 另一侧一直面对太阳
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.33,0:07:49.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样做会带来很多有趣的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.20,0:07:53.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为通常航天器都要做好温度控制 保持一切设备在正确温度下
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:57.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,而当光学元件保持低温的时候 就再也不用担心它的温度波动了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.63,0:08:00.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样把它设定到目标温度后就可以让它开始干活了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.88,0:08:05.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这会带来很多有趣的工程上的难题 我们会在未来几章的视频中提到
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.86,0:08:10.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,相对平凡一点的东西 就是面向太阳一侧的东西了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.49,0:08:24.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,遮阳罩这边有元件舱 有航电 供电 发动机 燃料罐 无线电收发装置和计算机
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.12,0:08:28.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,各种维持望远镜运营的东西都在这边
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.35,0:08:33.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,固定航天器姿态也是在这边吗? 比如说动量轮?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.51,0:08:38.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,对 动量轮也在这边 用来让望远镜指向特定方向
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.32,0:08:41.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,这还有火箭发动机 有两个作用
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:44.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,一方面是维持轨道 因为它的轨道是不稳定轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.80,0:08:51.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,另一方面是要卸载动量轮 因为动量轮会一直积累角动量
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:54.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,而那些角动量是哪来的? 是太阳光
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.64,0:08:57.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,它会轻微推动望远镜 导致它不平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.77,0:09:02.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以这两件事让望远镜需要燃料维持
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.13,0:09:04.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这也决定了这架望远镜的观测寿命
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.66,0:09:07.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,刚刚那段信息量不小 但我相信大家能听懂
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.03,0:09:08.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,我慢慢讲
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.48,0:09:09.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,动量轮 可老厉害了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:13.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,我几年前做过一期很细致的视频讲这个 但其大致思想
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:17.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,就是不用火箭发动机就能让航天器保持一定指向 像空中的猫一样
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:19.25,辉注,,0,0,0,,av16647535
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:19.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,强烈建议回头看看那个视频
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.25,0:09:22.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,一提到动量轮 我经常举的例子是摩托车
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.19,0:09:24.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,这段远古视频就能很好说明
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.26,0:09:27.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,摩托车运动员腾空的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.31,0:09:29.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,就相当于处于失重状态
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.95,0:09:35.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,但骑手可以通过拉刹车或者轰油门来控制自己抬头还是压低
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.43,0:09:38.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果他们轰油门 车头就会拉起
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.17,0:09:42.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为后轮的旋转会给车一个相反方向的扭矩
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:49.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果车手想低头 拉刹车就好了 后轮转速降低 车身就会压低
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:51.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,放在太空望远镜上也是一样的道理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.97,0:09:55.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过上面装的不是摩托车
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.07,0:09:58.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,而是几个不同方向持续旋转的电子飞轮
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.00,0:10:00.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,控制它们旋转的加速减速
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.15,0:10:02.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,就能把角动量转递给整个望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.43,0:10:10.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,几个飞轮的转速控制组合起来就能精确控制整个航天器的指向
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.91,0:10:16.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST的另一个有趣的冷知识是我们虽然想让它指向特定方向
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.24,0:10:18.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,但它却持续会受到太阳方向的压力
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:20.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,成为太阳光压
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.67,0:10:23.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,简单来讲就是太阳发出的光和各种电磁波会打在望远镜上
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.85,0:10:27.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,会给望远镜施加一个压力 有点像帆船
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.09,0:10:28.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个压力非常非常小
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:32.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,一平米的面积大概只有千分之一克的数量级
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:38.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在太空里 真空的零重力环境下 再微小的力也能影响很多事情
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:40.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,这是绝对不能忽视的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.90,0:10:44.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,来到望远镜的背后 这段黑色的部分 图里看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.43,0:10:47.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,主镜背面是一大块的设备组件
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.82,0:10:51.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括相机和光谱仪
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:57.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,可覆盖频段从人眼能看到的0.6微米波长的可见光
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.32,0:11:01.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,到人眼不可见的波长28微米的红外光
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.25,0:11:04.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,博士刚刚说到光谱仪波长范围从0.6微米到28微米
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.68,0:11:08.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,指的是望远镜能探测到的波长范围
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.02,0:11:11.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,这意味着望远镜只能看到可见光中红色的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:14.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,同时还能继续看到红外波段的内容
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.21,0:11:18.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,选择观测如此大范围的红外波段 肯定是出于某种考虑
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:20.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,而博士稍后也会提到这些
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:28.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以我们还有光谱仪 能探测到星光中的各种颜色分量
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:31.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,从观测到的结果来了解物体内部发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.94,0:11:34.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,首先我们想知道的是它是由什么物质组成的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.90,0:11:38.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以要找的是谱线
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.62,0:11:42.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,而谱线来自于不同化学元素 不同分子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.33,0:11:50.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,就好像7月4号五颜六色的烟花一样 每种都是来自不同的物质
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.55,0:11:54.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,-但这不太一样吧 因为光谱会红移吧？ -没错
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.02,0:11:57.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,那您是怎么知道红移后的光谱是自己想找的东西？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.95,0:12:01.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们实际上找的是某种特定的图案
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:06.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果看到的是单独一条谱线 那你没法百分之百确认是什么物质
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:13.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以真想百分之百确定观测到的是什么物质 就必须找两条或更多的谱线
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.43,0:12:19.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这也说明了一个事实 就是那些正在靠近我们或者远离我们的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.18,0:12:25.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,都实实在在参与了整个宇宙的膨胀 而这会大幅度改变我们观测到的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.92,0:12:30.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,远离我们的物体 观测到的波长会变长
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:33.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个波长的变化就叫红移
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:39.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以是零 如果物体在向我们移动那还可以是负的 还可以是很大的数字
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.73,0:12:47.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们曾经用望远镜观测到的最大红移是11
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.25,0:12:51.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,意思是我们观测到的波长是它发出的光的波长的12倍
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.83,0:12:54.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,-哦所以这个数字是倍数关系? -没错
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.68,0:13:00.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以比如说莱曼谱线阿尔法 波长是0.12微米
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.94,0:13:03.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,等我们观测到的时候已经变成1.44微米了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:05.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,这也是为什么红外波段观测如此重要
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.08,0:13:06.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为各种观测结果都会红移
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.68,0:13:11.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,没错 所以想要观测各种对象都被红移了的遥远宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.52,0:13:16.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,就必须有一台红外望远镜 才能研究那些早期是紫外光波段的目标
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:20.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,我插一句 您刚刚说红移了11倍波长
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.44,0:13:24.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,是不是意味着望远镜上的传感器能探测到超过11倍波长的范围?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:29.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,是的 而这也取决于观测物体发出光时的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:37.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果是某个特定的谱线 比如氢原子的莱曼阿尔法谱线 红移11倍
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.10,0:13:41.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,那就是原来波长的11倍 1.44微米
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:46.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,但如果假定宇宙中有更远的物体存在
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.42,0:13:49.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,那我们就能看到更大程度的红移
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.91,0:13:55.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们目前预期目标是想看到红移20-30倍的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:58.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,-你是不是特别期待? -那是相当期待啊!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.48,0:14:01.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,目前还没人观测到 但预测是存在的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.10,0:14:03.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们对其中某些预测还是很有信心的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.99,0:14:05.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,好吧 我的相机又过热了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:08.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,但现在咱们刚好可以聊聊红移
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.03,0:14:11.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,其实大家都体验过汽车喇叭的多普勒效应
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.49,0:14:14.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,当救护车或者汽车鸣笛向你驶来的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:19.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,你会听到稍高的声调 但当汽车远离你的时候 声调就会降低
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:22.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,当声源向你移动的时候 声波等效于被压缩
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.90,0:14:25.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以你耳朵听到的结果就是频率变高
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.48,0:14:30.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,而声源远离你的时候 声波就等效于被拉伸 听起来频率就会变低
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.96,0:14:32.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于光来说也是同理
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.29,0:14:38.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于一个远离我们的恒星发出的光来说 我们看到的光等效于被拉伸
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.88,0:14:40.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,就像汽车喇叭声调降低一样
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.64,0:14:46.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,观测到的光的频率也会降低 会从可见光波段降低到红外波段
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.33,0:14:48.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以如果我们看去观测红外波段
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:53.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,就相当于看不到那些原本发出可见光、在远离我们的星星
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.01,0:14:54.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就是红移
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.29,0:14:56.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,而对于持续膨胀的宇宙来说
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.10,0:15:01.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们观测到的很多物体都在慢慢远离我们
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.20,0:15:04.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此观测红外波段是非常重要的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.45,0:15:06.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,- So this is a giant tripod. There's three legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:10.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,The hinge points here, here, here, here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.51,0:15:13.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,and this leg folds in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.69,0:15:14.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,And here's a hinge point.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:17.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,So to get this ready for launch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:19.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,we pull this one out sideways.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.91,0:15:22.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,So you can pull the mirror up here and the legs
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.78,0:15:26.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,actually fold around behind the observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:27.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,So it just fits.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:29.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] You had a glimmer in your eye when you said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.90,0:15:32.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's a big deal. - That's a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.60,0:15:33.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,And it's one of many things
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.79,0:15:34.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,that have to work when you launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:37.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,Of course, everything is folded up for launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:40.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,Everything has to unfold and do the right thing out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.21,0:15:42.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,So of course the big question everyone has is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:43.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,are you sure it's going to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.81,0:15:46.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,And the answer is, so of course you can't be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.62,0:15:49.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,But we are doing what we should be doing to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.65,0:15:51.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,So what do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.67,0:15:53.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,Well, number one, you have two of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:54.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,when you possibly can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.34,0:15:56.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,So you get two shots when you need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.17,0:15:58.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,You rehearse everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.45,0:16:00.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,You practice and practice and practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.32,0:16:02.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,And you have grouchy people come to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.81,0:16:04.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,when you're not doing it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.33,0:16:07.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's really important because we hate doing it wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:09.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,even if we don't like being told.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.01,0:16:09.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] What are those people?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.84,0:16:11.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,The quality assurance officers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.23,0:16:14.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Those are review panels. We get peer reviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.56,0:16:16.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,We get senior engineers that have done
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:18.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,something related before that have
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.33,0:16:19.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,a good instinct about these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.56,0:16:22.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,They say, "No, don't do it like that. Do it some other way."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.71,0:16:27.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,But the most important thing is you test and test and test.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.41,0:16:29.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,Because there's no such thing as analyzing anything
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.95,0:16:31.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,well enough that you can be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.62,0:16:32.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] You know, you have destructive tests
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.87,0:16:34.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,and non-destructive tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.53,0:16:36.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,So how do you perform a test
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.18,0:16:38.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,when you only have one test article?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:40.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Well, we actually made several test articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.34,0:16:42.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,We made a pathfinder for the telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.36,0:16:46.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,with the carbon fiber framework and we put on
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.95,0:16:49.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,two of the mirrors or even finally three.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:51.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,- And my camera overheated again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.27,0:16:52.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,At this point, I'm starting to get embarrassed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.83,0:16:55.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,but don't worry about it, this gives us an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:56.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,as the camera cools off to get distracted
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.81,0:16:58.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,by cool things at NASA.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.02,0:16:59.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,This interview took place at NASA's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.53,0:17:02.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.13,0:17:04.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,which is where they've been controlling
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.68,0:17:06.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,the Hubble Space Telescope for the last several decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:07.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,I spoke to the Hubble operations manager
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.81,0:17:09.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,and got to see the actual control room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.99,0:17:11.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's a topic for another day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.06,0:17:13.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,but they do all kinds of awesome stuff here at Goddard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.60,0:17:15.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,So you're gonna make this Space Telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.52,0:17:17.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,and you're gonna put it up into space, you don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:21.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,the first time it sees a vacuum or near absolute zero
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.99,0:17:23.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,on the sensor side, you don't want that to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.95,0:17:26.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,for the first time in space so you got to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.10,0:17:28.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,try to simulate that on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.25,0:17:31.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,How do you do these incredibly physically challenging things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.57,0:17:34.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,here on one atmosphere on the surface of earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.49,0:17:37.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,The answer is a huge thermal vacuum that was built
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.52,0:17:39.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,at Goddard back in the 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.64,0:17:41.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,And it's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:42.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] So basically a large vacuum
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:44.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they pump liquid nitrogen into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.59,0:17:46.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] To make it cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:47.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] Make it cold, make it simulate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.43,0:17:49.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,the environment of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.62,0:17:51.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.37,0:17:52.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,So this is how you simulate space on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.51,0:17:55.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,- That's right. This is what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.79,0:17:57.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.60,0:17:59.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] I love the legacy look of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:02.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] It looks like a boiler, but backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.41,0:18:05.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's made to keep pressure out instead of contain pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.75,0:18:08.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] All designed on paper back in the sixties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.22,0:18:10.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,Think about it, like, that's all analog.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.72,0:18:13.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Okay, so we're on the top floor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.29,0:18:14.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,We are walking towards
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.13,0:18:16.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,the top of the thermal vacuum chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.44,0:18:19.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's cool. So do they actually put James Webb in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:20.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Some of the components.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:22.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,Before they assemble it they would take
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.87,0:18:24.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,some of the large components into this on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.70,0:18:26.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then we have much smaller ones over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.47,0:18:28.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,They test everything all the way down to the nuts and bolts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:30.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,These are also thermal vacuum chambers, just smaller scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:34.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Oh, this is for component level stuff. Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:36.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] Nuts and bolts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.21,0:18:37.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Nuts and bolts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.05,0:18:39.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] And smaller assembly parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.05,0:18:40.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Oh, that's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.15,0:18:42.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,They've got the hydraulic diagram integrated to the valves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:43.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's pretty neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.35,0:18:45.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Darryl] Where do you think that was printed? Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.15,0:18:47.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Oh wow. My bad got a little bit distracted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:49.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,The next thing they want to test for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:51.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,are the launch forces that happen on the rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.78,0:18:53.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,They have a huge centrifuge at Goddard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.87,0:18:56.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they can place instruments on that and simulate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:58.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,the G-forces that the telescope will see during launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:00.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's pretty awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:01.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then there's the vibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.90,0:19:02.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,that'll happen during launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.73,0:19:03.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is the shaker table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:06.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,So the Aerion is gonna to shake violently.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:09.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,What you have to do is you have to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:10.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,that the telescope isn't going to break during launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:13.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,So here at Goddard Space Center, check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:15.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's a really cool area here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.10,0:19:17.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is the way they test that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.00,0:19:18.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,They'll put the telescope here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.90,0:19:20.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,they'll mount it in position.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.12,0:19:22.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then they'll shake it violently to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.20,0:19:23.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,that nothing falls apart, nothing breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.83,0:19:25.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,Here's some B roll footage of them doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:29.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,The vibration testing. You can see the telescope shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:30.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm in a really neat spot right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:32.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is the tent that they move James Webb around with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.95,0:19:34.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's like a portable clean room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:36.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,And this is the sound chamber where
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:39.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,they're gonna acoustically load the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.01,0:19:40.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,What they're doing here is simulating
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:43.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,the roar of the rockets, which can get up over 140 decibels
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.80,0:19:45.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,and can be very destructive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.00,0:19:47.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,So they've got this big chamber with speakers in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.73,0:19:49.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,with a massive subwoofer and other speakers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.88,0:19:51.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,to blast it with sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.39,0:19:52.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's a subwoofer up top?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:55.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,- This is the largest subwoofer in the country
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.05,0:19:57.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,as far as I know, so if you really wanna drop the base
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.84,0:20:00.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,this is where you come. (Destin laughing)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.74,0:20:03.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,- The cool thing about a sound chamber is that the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:05.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,is different at different parts in the chamber
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.54,0:20:08.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,because you get reflections and echoes off the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:10.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,For example, if I have a sound wave going across
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.54,0:20:12.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,and bouncing off the wall, you might get
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.48,0:20:15.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,constructive interference, meaning you get a louder sound
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.29,0:20:18.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,at different points than you might get at quieter spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.54,0:20:23.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,So in order to test that, you can see, they have microphones
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.51,0:20:25.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,hanging at different points in the chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.94,0:20:30.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,Wow. I'm gonna get back behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.05,0:20:33.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,Because I don't want to interfere with what they're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.28,0:20:38.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,These people are moving this tent by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.56,0:20:41.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,And the way they're doing that is on an air bearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.73,0:20:46.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,They've got compressed air pumped to the feet of the tent
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:49.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,and a really flat surface floor and they're able
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.41,0:20:51.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,to move the whole thing by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.66,0:20:52.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,Here's a couple of really cool shots
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.97,0:20:54.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,where you can see people moving
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.82,0:20:57.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,the entire space telescope by hand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.80,0:21:00.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,within the portable cleaning room on a cushion of air.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.51,0:21:03.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine what you're thinking? This is so rad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.35,0:21:04.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,So my camera's overheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.72,0:21:07.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,Is that a problem on the telescope? (laughs)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.63,0:21:08.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,- No, the observatory doesn't overheat
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.95,0:21:11.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,because it's facing outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.35,0:21:13.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,The whole telescope is protected from the sunshine,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.65,0:21:16.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,from the earth and from the moon all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.13,0:21:17.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,by this giant sun shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.73,0:21:20.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,And we chose the orbit specially so we could do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.87,0:21:24.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,The Lagrange Point Two orbit that we choose is actually
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:28.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,the only place you can go where the single sided umbrella
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:31.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,that we build can protect the observatory completely
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.77,0:21:33.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,from all of those things at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.36,0:21:35.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Lagrange points are special points in space where
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.49,0:21:38.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,when you have two orbital bodies interacting with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.51,0:21:41.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,there's these little special spots where things
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.18,0:21:42.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,can kind of just balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.97,0:21:45.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,They're right in the sweet spot where they're being pulled
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.69,0:21:47.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,in two different directions at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.68,0:21:49.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,and they just kind of hover there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.86,0:21:50.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,Lagrange points are fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.85,0:21:52.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,There are five Lagrangian points
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.51,0:21:54.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,for any combination of two orbital bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.46,0:21:56.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,Since James Webb sensors could be affected
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.33,0:21:59.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,by earth shine and moon shine, L2 of the earth's sun system
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.82,0:22:01.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,is the optimum place for it to be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.58,0:22:04.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,and Dr. Mather is about to explain why.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.14,0:22:06.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,How are you going to communicate with it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.04,0:22:06.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,if it's on the other side of the moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.87,0:22:09.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Oh, it's not. We don't go to that exact spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.74,0:22:12.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,And of course the moon orbits as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.69,0:22:15.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] So are you orbiting a Lagrangian point?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:18.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,- You orbit around a Lagrange point, we don't go to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.29,0:22:21.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,Number one, it's easier to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.96,0:22:24.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,Number two, we want points in the shade.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.35,0:22:26.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,It's actually right behind the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.99,0:22:28.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,And most of the sunshine is being blocked by the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.83,0:22:31.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,at that spot so you don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.20,0:22:32.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Can you draw that for me on this piece of paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.62,0:22:37.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, so, sure. Here's the sun over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.91,0:22:43.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,Here's the earth over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.48,0:22:46.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,And not to scale, but here is the Lagrange point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.81,0:22:50.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,And we are going to be orbiting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.70,0:22:52.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,around a Lagrange point like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:54.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Just enough to get the sunshine around the earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.68,0:22:57.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,Where's the moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.19,0:22:59.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [John] The moon is a lot closer in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.93,0:23:03.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,My handwriting is not so good today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.44,0:23:05.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,But the Lagrange point's about four times
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.72,0:23:07.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,as far from the earth as the moon is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.33,0:23:08.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.90,0:23:10.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [John] So we never have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.96,0:23:12.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.33,0:23:14.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize that you were choosing the orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.29,0:23:17.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,I thought the whole point was to, yeah, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.77,0:23:19.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,- We need the sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.14,0:23:20.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.29,0:23:23.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,- We need solar power to run the observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.22,0:23:24.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Okay, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.91,0:23:26.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,- We need the sunshine. It also takes more fuel to get to.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.95,0:23:29.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] You don't have an RTG onboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.32,0:23:31.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,- No, we don't. There's no need for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.86,0:23:33.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,And that's hard to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.06,0:23:39.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,So we need several kilowatts of electricity, so sunshine--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.71,0:23:40.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Where are the solar panels?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.54,0:23:42.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Solar panels are hidden in this picture, but they are
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.56,0:23:46.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,obviously going to be on the sun side of the big sun shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.78,0:23:49.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,But a few kilowatts is actually small
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.26,0:23:50.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,for a giant observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.78,0:23:51.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.50,0:23:54.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,- That's 'cause what's over here on this side
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.04,0:23:56.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,doesn't use anything much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.43,0:23:58.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,Only a little bit of energy to run the detectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.96,0:24:00.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] I know you're excited
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.79,0:24:02.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,about what's gonna come out of the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.15,0:24:02.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.99,0:24:05.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,Who knows what's out there that we've never guessed at?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.30,0:24:07.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,We have wonderful way exciting things
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:08.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,to work on that we know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.82,0:24:11.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,The first stars and galaxies, the first black holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.57,0:24:14.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,how the galaxies grow, how stars are being born today
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.73,0:24:18.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,with planets around them and even planets around other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:21.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,and the outer solar system, where we learn something
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.57,0:24:23.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,about how solar systems work and maybe even
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.72,0:24:25.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,how come the earth is special or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.52,0:24:28.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,The web telescope will make beautiful pictures as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.59,0:24:29.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,They will be different, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.89,0:24:31.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,because we pick up light at different wavelengths,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.38,0:24:33.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,but those beautiful glowing gas clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:35.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,we'll see them too, just differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.86,0:24:38.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,We are, among other things, trying to see through
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.58,0:24:40.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,those glowing clouds to see what's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.65,0:24:42.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,So the stars that are being born inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:45.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,you can't see them directly right now because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.22,0:24:48.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,that dust and gas is obscuring them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.07,0:24:50.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,Infrared light that we will pick up can go
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.03,0:24:52.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,right around those dust grains and see inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.26,0:24:55.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,So our hope is that it'll look different and also beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.54,0:24:57.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] So you're saying the infrared light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.85,0:25:00.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,can go through those dust rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.53,0:25:02.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [John] Yes, infrared light, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.05,0:25:04.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,all light bounces off dust particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.54,0:25:06.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,but the longer the wavelength, the less bounce.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.97,0:25:07.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.66,0:25:11.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [John] So the infrared light can go through the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.51,0:25:14.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,that enables us to see things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.12,0:25:16.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Oh, that's a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.10,0:25:17.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,So what we'll probably be seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.51,0:25:19.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,is we'll take infrared images and then
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.23,0:25:21.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,we'll false color them so people can see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.06,0:25:23.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,these beautiful pictures that we've seen in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.63,0:25:24.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,That's exactly the plan? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.71,0:25:27.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] That's fantastic. Last question.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.01,0:25:28.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna do on launch day?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.70,0:25:31.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,- I'll either be at the launch site to cheer,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.86,0:25:34.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,or I'll be back here to talk to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.31,0:25:36.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,Don't know which one will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.29,0:25:37.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's such a limited number of people can go
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.95,0:25:40.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,to the launch site that the people who really need
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.01,0:25:41.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,to be there should be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.57,0:25:44.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Right, but are you, I mean, that's gotta be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.22,0:25:46.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,a very anxious moment for you, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.97,0:25:48.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.09,0:25:49.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] No?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.31,0:25:52.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,- I don't get anxious about stuff I can't deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.44,0:25:54.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] Can you kind of tell me why?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.97,0:25:57.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, so I'm not an anxious about things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.27,0:25:59.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,because I know that we're doing the right thing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.15,0:26:01.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,to make the best possible plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.94,0:26:03.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,So when somebody says "We should worry about this,"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.98,0:26:06.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,we worry about it and then we make a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.42,0:26:08.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,So when you're 70 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.39,0:26:09.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,you get tired of worrying about stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.68,0:26:11.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,You just say, "We'll make a plan."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.29,0:26:13.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,- [Destin] I see. And you accept what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.33,0:26:14.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.36,0:26:16.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,- That's interesting. That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.75,0:26:19.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,I really liked that. (laughs)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.32,0:26:22.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is Dr. John Mather and I cannot thank you enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.86,0:26:24.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,- Destin, a pleasure to talk with you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.45,0:26:26.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,and look forward to seeing what you make.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.70,0:26:29.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,- I thought this conversation was fascinating
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.95,0:26:31.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,on so many different levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.12,0:26:33.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,I came into it expecting to learn about science
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.61,0:26:37.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,and astronomy and how different things work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.14,0:26:41.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,But I left with a sense of, it's like a nugget of wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.78,0:26:43.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,that Dr. Mather dropped on us there at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.83,0:26:44.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.74,0:26:47.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,This is one of the most complicated things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.03,0:26:49.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,that humans have ever done.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.05,0:26:50.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's a lot riding on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.94,0:26:53.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,There is a tremendous amount of investment of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.85,0:26:57.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,money, human lives, my family included.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.08,0:26:58.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's a lot riding on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.57,0:27:01.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,But when I asked him, "Well, aren't you worried?"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.62,0:27:04.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,He said, "No, because I've made the best possible plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.97,0:27:06.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,We've done our best."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.74,0:27:08.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,And then he just releases it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.41,0:27:11.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,He's literally going to let it ride on a rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.32,0:27:13.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,There's some deep wisdom there
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.40,0:27:15.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,that I'm going to apply to my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.45,0:27:18.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,If the man that's over one of the most difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.66,0:27:21.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,scientific endeavors that humans have ever done
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.02,0:27:23.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,can make the best possible plan and then not worry
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.78,0:27:26.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,and then emotionally release that to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.33,0:27:28.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,"We did our best. Let's see what happens."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.11,0:27:30.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,If he can do that with this project,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.21,0:27:32.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,how can I apply that to my own life?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.62,0:27:34.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I thought that was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.38,0:27:36.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,I thought it was super deep wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.10,0:27:39.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,And perhaps that would be helpful for you as it is for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.94,0:29:15.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,In an upcoming video we're gonna learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.91,0:29:18.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,about the James Webb Space Telescope from my dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.37,0:29:20.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,who actually worked on the sun shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.39,0:29:22.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,Very excited to share this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.06,0:29:25.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,It was exciting for me to be able to go to see my dad
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.60,0:29:28.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,do one of the coolest things that humans have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.29,0:29:29.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,I don't know. And this is my dad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.94,0:29:31.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,I'm really excited about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.23,0:29:33.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,So I'll share that with you in an upcoming video.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.84,0:29:37.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,And I hope you enjoyed this interview with Dr. John Mather.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.92,0:29:40.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,I'm Destin. You're getting smarter every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.24,0:29:41.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,Have a good one. Bye.
